1
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:34,950
[Unbreakable Ⅱ]

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:37,860
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:38,759 --> 00:01:39,840
The key now is

4
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:43,280
how we can legally and cleverly

5
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,870
distribute the assets.

6
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:47,320
Is it correct for me to understand it this way?

7
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:47,870
Well,

8
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:50,350
I'm thinking of giving my assets to my dad,

9
00:01:50,350 --> 00:01:51,220
do you think that works?

10
00:01:51,289 --> 00:01:52,420
That won't work.

11
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,560
The direct line of relatives

12
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,070
is too obvious.

13
00:01:56,070 --> 00:01:57,200
Once they look into it, it'll be easy to find.

14
00:01:58,789 --> 00:01:59,950
Is there anyone that

15
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,920
both of you trust completely

16
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,540
and

17
00:02:02,570 --> 00:02:04,570
who hasn't been involved in this matter at all?

18
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,280
Hui,

19
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:09,539
we can transfer the money

20
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:14,290
to my third uncle's account.【】

21
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:16,310
We registered a new company

22
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:17,400
under his name recently

23
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,000
and opened a company account.

24
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:20,720
You know, my third uncle

25
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,260
can't even read,

26
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,329
he doesn't know anything—

27
00:02:24,490 --> 00:02:25,450
he just listens to my dad,

28
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,360
so it's definitely safe.

29
00:02:26,390 --> 00:02:29,110
But it's like giving the money to someone else.

30
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:32,450
So, Mr. Xue, do you think this will work?

31
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,090
This is your family matter;

32
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,200
how can I interfere?

33
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:36,350
It's up to you.

34
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:37,630
Let me remind you,

35
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:39,910
no matter who you transfer the money to,

36
00:02:40,170 --> 00:02:41,560
you need to leave some money

37
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:42,760
in your company's account.

38
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:44,360
At least let the court

39
00:02:44,650 --> 00:02:45,980
be able to enforce something,

40
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:46,520
right?

41
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:48,579
I think it works.

42
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,000
Then how about this?

43
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,360
Let's have Mr. Xue

44
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,960
represent us in this case.

45
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,800
You handle it alone, is that okay?

46
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:57,150
According to the law,

47
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,970
a lawyer can only represent one person.

48
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:00,190
Wait.

49
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:01,110
I'll represent Mr. Zhou,

50
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:02,130
and you find another lawyer to represent you.

51
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:04,920
Let's sign the agreement today.

52
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:05,700
Okay.

53
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:07,290
My agency fee is 300,000 yuan.

54
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,110
You see,

55
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:15,590
we are really in a tough spot right now.

56
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:17,670
We've been hiding and not doing any business,

57
00:03:17,690 --> 00:03:18,900
and honestly, we don't have much money.

58
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,950
Could you consider

59
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:23,430
giving us a discount?

60
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:28,000
The key is that I still have to design the path for property distribution

61
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,560
and risk isolation.

62
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:30,800
Anyway, if you don't

63
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,150
pay the money to me,

64
00:03:32,310 --> 00:03:34,650
you might end up losing it all to someone else in the future.

65
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:36,500
We're really in a tough spot right now, but...

66
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,770
We won't bargain.

67
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:39,390
We'd rather give it

68
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:40,800
to someone else

69
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:43,380
than to give it to the old lady.

70
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,320
Mr. Xue, I'll entrust this

71
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:46,540
to you.

72
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,150
Are you relieved now?

73
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:49,020
Yes.

74
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:50,400
Mr. Tian,

75
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:52,190
I'm telling you, the 300,000 yuan

76
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:53,400
is worth way more than

77
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:55,800
the 130,000 yuan we gave to Mr. Han.

78
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:56,840
Mr. Han

79
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:57,880
is just a big scammer.

80
00:03:58,570 --> 00:03:59,690
Don't forget that

81
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,630
it's me who recommended to you

82
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:02,000
such an excellent lawyer.

83
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:04,910
Mr. Tian, don't worry.

84
00:04:04,910 --> 00:04:06,310
We know what to do.

85
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,250
As long as the matter is settled,

86
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,320
we will reward you.

87
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:10,120
Thank you.

88
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:10,750
Don't worry.

89
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:11,910
How about this?

90
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:12,960
You two go first.

91
00:04:12,990 --> 00:04:13,540
I

92
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,400
have another case to introduce to Mr. Xue.

93
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:17,390
I was so happy that I forgot.

94
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,120
Okay.

95
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:18,600
Come on.

96
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,800
Go on with your work.

97
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:20,870
Thank you.

98
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:21,600
You're welcome.

99
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,390
Thank you.

100
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,190
Take care.

101
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,000
Mr. Xue.

102
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:36,800
Why are you back?

103
00:04:37,260 --> 00:04:38,010
Mr. Xue.

104
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:40,560
I have to thank Mr. Chen for the introduction;

105
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,659
otherwise, I wouldn't have had the chance to meet a senior like you.

106
00:04:42,690 --> 00:04:43,420
You're

107
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,520
so experienced and skillful.

108
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,560
I hope you'll guide me more in the future.

109
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:48,790
I wouldn't dare to guide you;

110
00:04:48,810 --> 00:04:50,290
you already have a mentor.

111
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,159
When it comes to experience and skills,

112
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,680
your mentor is much better than me.

113
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,159
He's not as good as you.

114
00:04:57,409 --> 00:04:59,880
Well, Mr. Xue,

115
00:04:59,909 --> 00:05:00,790
do we have any specified brokerage

116
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:03,450
in our firm

117
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:06,660
regarding cases that come through referrals?

118
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,050
Okay, got it.

119
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,290
I see.

120
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:11,670
Don't beat around the bush.

121
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:14,020
As for the referral fee, I'll give you 10%.

122
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:15,720
Mr. Xue.

123
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:16,570
You see,

124
00:05:16,690 --> 00:05:19,100
you're a respected senior in the industry,

125
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:21,920
so don't be too strict with me, a junior.

126
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,560
Ten percent

127
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:25,290
is a bit too low.

128
00:05:25,590 --> 00:05:26,520
How about

129
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,120
15%?

130
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,560
You're even greedier than your mentor.

131
00:05:33,659 --> 00:05:35,340
Okay, 15% is fine.

132
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,290
Are you relieved now?

133
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,390
Thank you, Mr. Xue.

134
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:38,830
Goodbye, Mr. Xue.

135
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,360
The defendant should

136
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,870
bear corresponding legal responsibility

137
00:05:51,270 --> 00:05:52,680
for escaping during his sentence

138
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,720
and committing additional crimes.

139
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:57,040
But we would like to particularly remind

140
00:05:57,159 --> 00:05:58,560
the court that

141
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,040
the defendant's actions

142
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:02,160
were driven by circumstances.

143
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:04,560
In light of the questioning of another defendant,

144
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:07,510
Ma Lili, it has been established that

145
00:06:08,010 --> 00:06:10,810
Ma Lili took advantage of Xu Jianshe's detention

146
00:06:10,830 --> 00:06:13,200
and his isolation from the outside world,

147
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,650
deceiving him

148
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,400
into believing

149
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,920
he had been subjected to unjust treatment.

150
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:21,370
This led Xu Jianshe to develop a mindset of escaping as a form of retaliation.

151
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:24,480
At the same time, Ma Lili also illegally controlled

152
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,920
Xu Jianshe's assets.

153
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:28,560
It was only after Xu Jianshe realized the truth

154
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:31,250
that he directed his retaliation toward Ma Lili.

155
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:35,110
Xu Jianshe should indeed face severe legal punishment

156
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:37,870
for committing another crime during his sentence,

157
00:06:37,950 --> 00:06:39,430
while the deception

158
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,680
and unlawful possession of his assets

159
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:44,070
by Ma Lili

160
00:06:44,090 --> 00:06:46,409
were significant contributing factors to the situation.

161
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,750
After learning the full facts,

162
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,360
Xu Jianshe has sincerely repented,

163
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,480
accepted legal consequences,

164
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,890
and is willing to cover

165
00:06:53,909 --> 00:06:56,120
the medical expenses of the victim, Ma Lili.

166
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:59,159
Here, on behalf of the defendant,

167
00:06:59,159 --> 00:07:01,560
we extend an apology to the victim,

168
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:03,520
express remorse to the court,

169
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:06,480
and hope that the court will take the aforementioned circumstances into account

170
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:09,240
during sentencing.

171
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,480
All rise.

172
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:17,560
In accordance with Articles 234

173
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,870
and 316

174
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:22,160
of the Criminal Law of the People's Republic of China,

175
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,750
the defendant, Xu Jianshe,

176
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:25,590
is hereby sentenced to death

177
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:27,620
with a two-year reprieve.

178
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:43,890
Xu Jianshe,

179
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:46,800
we're here to discuss your opinion on filing an appeal.

180
00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:48,360
Do you still want to appeal?

181
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:49,560
No.

182
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,630
Filing an appeal won't lead to a harsher sentence,

183
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:54,310
so you can take your time to think it through

184
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,360
before making a decision.

185
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:56,710
I know.

186
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,360
Honestly, I didn't expect to

187
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,360
be spared my life

188
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,480
when I went to court this time,

189
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:05,370
so I won't appeal.

190
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:08,860
I plead guilty and will work on reforming myself.

191
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:10,630
Thank you.

192
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,750
Your assets

193
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,880
are currently being managed by your cousin's family.

194
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,680
We've interacted with them a few times

195
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,890
and feel they can be trusted.

196
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,590
However, we'd like to remind you that

197
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,070
even while you're in prison,

198
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:23,830
you still have the right to manage your assets.

199
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,990
If you need assistance in this regard,

200
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,560
feel free to reach out to us

201
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,240
or another lawyer.

202
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,360
If needed,

203
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,270
I'll only turn to you.

204
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,909
Thank you for trusting us.

205
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:36,360
We'll go back and discuss it,

206
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:38,669
and next time we'll bring an agreement.

207
00:08:38,669 --> 00:08:39,260
Okay.

208
00:08:39,669 --> 00:08:42,360
We'll have many chances to stay in touch.

209
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,150
Take care.

210
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:46,400
Thank you.

211
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,120
Xu Jianshe,

212
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:50,360
who was the one

213
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:53,270
who dealt the fatal blow to Li Zhanjun

214
00:08:53,710 --> 00:08:54,580
in that case back then?

215
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,240
I need to correct something I said before.

216
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,630
What is it?

217
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,960
I once told you that

218
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:22,200
I don't like dealing with innocent clients.

219
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,080
When the client is innocent,

220
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,360
the pressure on the lawyer is much higher.

221
00:09:26,650 --> 00:09:27,960
But I've realized now that

222
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:29,470
even when the client isn't innocent,

223
00:09:29,490 --> 00:09:30,970
the lawyer won't be easy either.

224
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:33,720
He's clearly guilty,

225
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:36,070
and yet you help him get away with it.

226
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,270
Can you feel at peace with that

227
00:09:38,290 --> 00:09:39,350
after knowing the truth?

228
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,920
You're overthinking it.

229
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,560
Whether or not he was the one who struck the fatal blow,

230
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:46,260
this case accusing him of being the main culprit

231
00:09:46,290 --> 00:09:48,760
lacks solid evidence.

232
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,890
Even if we defended him

233
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,040
and won the case at the time,

234
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,080
as long as it complied with the legal principle

235
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,030
that facts must be clear and evidence must be sufficient,

236
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:58,320
the prosecution would still strengthen their evidence

237
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,690
in the later stages of the trial.

238
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:01,120
Isn't this precisely the point

239
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,520
of the adversarial system in law?

240
00:10:05,390 --> 00:10:06,070
Forget about it.

241
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:08,870
Anyway, we've helped someone

242
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:10,550
and made money.

243
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,750
Auntie Song's case has been announced,

244
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:15,080
but the trial won't be scheduled

245
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,230
for at least 60 days.

246
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,720
If we can manage

247
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,750
Xu Jianshe's assets,

248
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,550
we'll have a steady income.

249
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,510
Let's find an office as soon as possible.

250
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:25,960
These days,

251
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,820
I feel like I'm living in the office;

252
00:10:27,850 --> 00:10:29,250
there's no privacy at all.

253
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:46,810
Hello, Ms. Luo.

254
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:47,550
Feng.

255
00:10:47,670 --> 00:10:49,270
These are Ms. Qiu and Ms. Xia.

256
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:50,120
Hello, Ms. Qiu, Ms. Xia.

257
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:50,890
This way, please.

258
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,270
Please come in.

259
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,850
Why are you here again?

260
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,720
Instead of thinking of ways to deliver the summons,

261
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:15,130
why are you running over here?

262
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,280
What a waste of time.

263
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,240
Manager Feng,

264
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,360
which floor

265
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,550
is the property I want to see on?

266
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:21,840
On the 17th floor, Ms. Luo.

267
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,240
Speaking of which, you have really good taste.

268
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,260
A law firm is just downstairs.

269
00:11:25,910 --> 00:11:26,540
What?

270
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,670
You want to rent the 17th floor?

271
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:30,780
Director Han, are you talking to me?

272
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:33,810
Yes, let's go and have a look. It's not decided yet.

273
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:35,590
What's the deal, Director Han? Are you not happy about it?

274
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:38,920
No, no complaints at all.

275
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:39,630
But, when it comes to it,

276
00:11:39,630 --> 00:11:41,320
if I do end up renting the 17th floor,

277
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:44,400
you're just below me.

278
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:45,930
It looks like we're really destined to be neighbors.

279
00:11:57,420 --> 00:11:59,180
Why put yourself through this?

280
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,920
Just a rehearsal.

281
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,890
Dreams will always come true.

282
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:04,980
Yes.

283
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,760
Please.

284
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,460
Ms. Luo,

285
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,190
